  "prompt": "Are there alternatives to Yelp?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several alternatives to Yelp that you can consider for finding reviews and information about local businesses. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Google Reviews**: Often integrated with Google Maps, this platform allows users to leave reviews and ratings for businesses directly through Google.\n\n2. **TripAdvisor**: Primarily focused on travel-related businesses, TripAdvisor offers reviews for restaurants, hotels, attractions, and activities.\n\n3. **Zomato**: Originally focused on restaurants, Zomato provides user-generated reviews, menus, and photos.\n\n4. **Facebook**: Many businesses have pages where customers can leave reviews and ratings, making Facebook a useful platform for finding local recommendations.\n\n5. **Angie\u2019s List**: Originally a subscription-based service, it now offers reviews and ratings for various service-oriented businesses.\n\n6. **Foursquare**: Users can check in to locations and leave reviews, though it's more focused on discovering places rather than solely on reviews.\n\n7. **OpenTable**: Primarily for restaurant reservations, OpenTable also features customer reviews regarding their dining experiences.\n\n8. **Nextdoor**: A neighborhood-based platform where users can get recommendations and reviews from people living in their vicinity.\n\n9. **Trustpilot**: Though focused more on online businesses, it provides reviews and ratings for various services and products.\n\n10. **Gaia**: A platform focused on holistic and alternative wellness businesses, allowing users to share experiences and ratings.\n\nEach platform has its unique features and focus areas, so the best choice may depend on the type of business you are looking to review or find.",
